data.name: Spicy Black Bean and Sweet Potato Tacos with Avocado Crema
data.quickTastyDescription: Flavorful and hearty tacos filled with spiced black beans and roasted sweet potatoes, topped with a creamy avocado sauce.
detailedCookingInstructions: Toss cubed sweet potatoes with olive oil, cumin, chili powder, and salt. Spread them on a baking sheet and roast for about 25 minutes until tender.
In a small bowl, combine black beans (drained and rinsed), chopped cilantro, lime juice, and garlic. Mash slightly with a fork.
For the avocado crema, blend avocado, lime juice, garlic, and a pinch of salt until smooth.
Warm the corn tortillas in a skillet or directly over the flame until pliable.
Assemble the tacos by layering the sweet potatoes, black bean mixture, and a drizzle of avocado crema on each tortilla.
